<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <title>Read Receipt</title>
</head>

<body>
  <p>Hey ðŸ‘‹</p>
  <p>
    You received this email because your email address was entered into the tool <a href="{{domain}}">Read Receipt</a>
    created by <a href="https://tobysmith.uk">Toby Smith</a> and you opened an email containing a tracking pixel.
  </p>

  <p>
    Below shows all of the information which my implementation of a tracking pixel is able to expose. Note that other
    people or companies may be able to find out more!
  </p>

  <p>
    Times:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>First email sent at: {{times.firstEmailTimestamp}}</li>
    <li>This email sent at: {{times.secondEmailTimestamp}}</li>
    <li>Time difference: {{times.timestampDifference}}</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    You:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Email: {{user.email}}</li>
    <li>IP Address: {{user.ip}}</li>
  </ul>

  {{#if ipData}}
  <p>
    Your <b>approximate</b> location:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>{{ipData.city}}</li>
    <li>{{ipData.zip}}</li>
    <li>{{ipData.regionName}} ({{ipData.region}})</li>
    <li>{{ipData.country}} ({{ipData.countryCode}})</li>
    <p>
      <li>Lat: {{ipData.lat}}, Lon: {{ipData.lon}}</li>
    </p>
  </ul>

  <p>
    Your connection:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Is Mobile: {{ipData.mobile}}</li>
    <li>Is via Proxy: {{ipData.proxy}}</li>
    <li>Internet provider: {{ipData.isp}}</li>
  </ul>
  {{/if}}

  {{#if userAgentData}}
  <p>
    Your device:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Browser: {{userAgentData.browser}}</li>
    <li>Version: {{userAgentData.version}}</li>
    <li>Operating System: {{userAgentData.os}}</li>
    <li>Platform: {{userAgentData.platform}}</li>
  </ul>
  {{/if}}

  <p>
    Some of this information may be inaccurate, especially the location and device sections. This is because some
    providers attempt to protect their users from tools like the tracking pixel hidden in the first email.
  </p>

  <p>
    Reopening the first email you received on different devices or by enabling/disabling WiFi on mobile devices will
    yield different results with different levels of data accuracy. If you have multiple emails from different providers
    you will see different results from each of them too, eg, @outlook.com or @gmail.com.
  </p>

  <p>
    This tool stores <b>none</b> of your personal information. It's totally stateless with no cookies,
    databases, logs, or anything else! You can check the source code on
    <a target="_blank" rel="noopener" href="https://github.com/tobysmith568/Read-Receipt">my GitHub</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    If you have any questions, you can reach out to me at <a
      href="mailto:tobysmith568@hotmail.co.uk">tobysmith568@hotmail.co.uk</a> or find me at <a
      href="https://tobysmith.uk">https://tobysmith.uk</a>.
  </p>

  <p>
    Thanks!
  </p>
</body>

</html>
